[
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"519727\">@Alice Ryhl</span> <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"411477\">@Miguel Ojeda</span></p>\n<p>Follow up from the discussion yesterday; notes from the meeting:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">MyDriver</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">MyModule</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"n\">_driver</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Registration</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">pci</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">Adapter</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">MyDriver</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">};</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">pci</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">Driver</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">MyDriver</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">..</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">InPlaceModule</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">MyModule</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">..</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">module</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"k\">type</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">MyModule</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"o\">..</span><span class=\"p\">.</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">module_pci_driver</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">type</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">MyDriver</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">..</span><span class=\"p\">.</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<ul>\n<li><code>module_*_driver!</code>'s type argument is the actual driver type, whereas</li>\n<li><code>module!</code>'s type argument is the type implementing <code>InPlaceModule</code></li>\n</ul>\n<p><div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ModuleMetadata</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"n\">type_</span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">const</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">NAME</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"nb\">static</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">CStr</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c_str</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"fm\">env!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"KBUILD_MODNAME\"</span><span class=\"p\">));</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">PartOfModule</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">MyDriver</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Module</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">MyModule</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">PartOfModule</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">MyModule</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Module</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">MyModule</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div><br>\n</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>There is a little bit of an inconvenience with the discussed solution:</p>\n<p>Drivers using the <code>module_*_driver!</code> macros all end up with the exact same type implementing <code>InPlaceModule</code>, see <a href=\"https://github.com/Rust-for-Linux/linux/commit/0fcde4fb43f36673cac188e339f09503cf109b18#diff-4318897edaeb5a4bc0ad9547ff7a7219463aee9c44bab91f13c8bf543bc62926R89\">[1]</a>.</p>\n<p>Obviously, we can't implement <code>ModuleMetadata</code> in <code>module!</code> for this type, since <code>module!</code> is called for every driver. Or in other words, the discussed solution requires a unique module type per module, but the <code>module_*_driver!</code> macros use a common type.</p>\n<p>The obvious solution would be to get rid of <code>kernel::driver::Module</code> and instead generate a new module type within the <code>module_*_driver!</code> macros, which kinda sucks a bit.</p>\n<p>(I wonder if passing through the module name in <code>Module::init</code> was that bad of an idea.)</p>\n<p>Any ideas?</p>\n<p>[1] <a href=\"https://github.com/Rust-for-Linux/linux/commit/0fcde4fb43f36673cac188e339f09503cf109b18#diff-4318897edaeb5a4bc0ad9547ff7a7219463aee9c44bab91f13c8bf543bc62926R89\">https://github.com/Rust-for-Linux/linux/commit/0fcde4fb43f36673cac188e339f09503cf109b18#diff-4318897edaeb5a4bc0ad9547ff7a7219463aee9c44bab91f13c8bf543bc62926R89</a></p>",
        "id": 488606083,
        "sender_full_name": "Danilo Krummrich",
        "timestamp": 1734001407
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Right, so you're running into the orphan rule.</p>",
        "id": 488611269,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1734003069
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Just make the macro emit a struct.</p>",
        "id": 488611294,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1734003081
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If we keep the <code>name</code> argument in <code>Registration::new</code>,  which is probably cleaner, since it doesn't always hard code the name in the bus abstractions, we don't even need <code>PartOfModule</code> for now, since we know the module type in <code>module_driver!</code>.</p>",
        "id": 488634483,
        "sender_full_name": "Danilo Krummrich",
        "timestamp": 1734010421
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"411477\">@Miguel Ojeda</span>  I also think we don't necessarily need <code>env!(KBUILD_MODNAME)</code>, we can just keep using the <code>name</code> argument of <code>module!</code>.</p>",
        "id": 488635104,
        "sender_full_name": "Danilo Krummrich",
        "timestamp": 1734010608
    }
]